item.description:
In Art Carpenter’s latest book, Carpenter&#8217;s Guide to Innovative SAS Techniques, a data step approach to transpose data (from long to wide) works like (Ch2.4.2):

 data tst; &#160;&#160;&#160; input type $ grp value $3.; datalines; A 1 a A 2 aa A 3 aaa B 1 b B 2 bb B 3 bbb C 1 c C 2 cc C 3 ccc ;
data art(keep=type grp1-grp3); &#160;&#160; set tst; &#160;&#160; by type; &#160;&#160; retain grp1-grp3 ; &#160;&#160; array grps {3} $ grp1-grp3; &#160;&#160; if first.
